operational_notes.bt_template_hint:
Two concrete examples. First when current == correct (tickle), second when current != correct (bubble-sort drags). Coords shown are for THIS consult's tree.json (grip centers at y=450, 502, 553, x=687). REPLACE with current tree.json bboxes on each consultation.

```json
{
  "type": "sequence",
  "_comment": "CASE A: current top-to-bottom order MATCHES correct order — single tickle drag at mid item engages widget without reorder, then click Check.",
  "children": [
    {
      "type": "action",
      "action": "drag",
      "params": {
        "start": {"x": 687, "y": 502},
        "end":   {"x": 687, "y": 502},
        "post_delay": 0.6
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "action",
      "action": "wait_for_element",
      "params": {"role": "AXButton", "target": "Check", "max_wait": 3.0}
    },
    {
      "type": "action",
      "action": "find_and_click",
      "params": {"target": "Check", "role": "AXButton", "strategy": "mouse_click", "match_mode": "exact", "post_delay": 2.5}
    },
    {
      "type": "action",
      "action": "store_qa",
      "params": {"question": "Rank by question criterion (greatest first)", "answer": "G,B,R", "question_type": "solve_complex"}
    }
  ]
}
```

